        <Parent_String>seminaries (buildings) [300386971], religious schools (buildings) [300448956], school buildings by subject [300006525], schools (buildings) [300006495], academic buildings [300444406], institutional buildings [300132384], single built works by function [300004894], single built works by specific type [300004795], single built works (built environment) [300004790], Single Built Works (hierarchy name) [300004789], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Buildings that house schools providing education in, for example, theology and religious history, primarily, but not exclusively, to prepare students for jobs as priests, ministers, or church workers; usually sponsored or controlled by a church or other religious organization. For buildings that house schools devoted especially to the training of rabbis, use "rabbinical seminaries."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Escuela que proporciona educación en teología e historia religiosa, principalmente aunque no de un modo exclusivo, para preparar a los estudiantes en los oficios de sacerdotes, ministros o trabajadores de iglesia. Generalmente, patrocinada o controlada por una iglesia u otra organización religiosa. Para escuelas dedicadas especialmente a la enseñanza de los rabinos, empléese "seminario rabínico".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Scholen die onderwijs bieden in theologie en religieuze geschiedenis, met als belangrijkste, maar niet als enige doelstelling het voorbereiden van de studenten op werk als priester, predikant of kerkmedewerker; worden meestal gesteund en beheerd door een kerk of een andere religieuze organisatie. Gebruik 'rabbijnenscholen' voor scholen die zijn gewijd aan het opleiden van rabbi's.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>提供與神學和宗教歷史相關之教育的學校，其最主要目的是協助學生未來從事牧師、神職人員或教堂工作者等職業作準備，然而這點並非其唯一目的；此學校通常由教堂或其他宗教組織加以贊助或管理。若指稱專門培訓拉比的學校，則使用「拉比神學院」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gebäude, in dem eine Schule untergebracht ist, die hauptsächlich, aber nicht ausschließlich, eine Ausbildung für beispielsweise Theologie- und Religionsgeschichte anbietet, um die Studenten für den Beruf des Priesters, Pfarrers oder kirchlichen Mitarbeiters vorzubereiten; gewöhnlich von einer Kirche oder einer anderen religiösen Organisation unterstützt oder kontrolliert. Für ein Gebäude, in dem eine Schule untergebracht ist, die sich insbesondere der Ausbildung von Rabbinern widmet, siehe "Rabbinerseminar".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
